# Leak patterns — strings that must never appear in commit messages.
#
# Copy this file to .leak-patterns.local (which is gitignored) and list
# identifiers you don't want in the public commit log: personal emails,
# pet names, family names, client names, internal project codes, private
# repo references, etc.
#
# One pattern per line. Lines starting with # are ignored. Patterns are
# matched case-insensitively as extended regex (grep -iE).
#
# The .githooks/commit-msg hook reads this file and blocks any commit
# whose message matches a pattern.
#
# Examples (uncomment and customize):
#
# your-personal-email@example.com
# pet-name
# family-last-name
# internal-project-codename
# your-github-org/private-repo
